<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1600,1735]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1636,1662]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is easily distinguished from all its congeners by the elytra with two yellowish brown markings and the aedeagus without pubescence. The female is unknown.
</paragraph>
